{"word":"χρυσός","slug":"χρυσός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>χρυσός, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [Semitic loanword]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> the precious metal known as <b>gold <a href='B:470 2:11'>Mt 2:11</a>; <a href='B:530 3:12'>1 Cor 3:12</a>; <a href='B:730 9:7'>Rv 9:7</a>; <a href='B:730 18:12'>18:12</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘object made of gold or decorated with gold’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> personal gold adornment, <b>gold ornament(s), jewelry <a href='B:610 2:9'>1 Ti 2:9</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>; <a href='B:730 17:4'>Rv 17:4</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>; <a href='B:730 18:16'>18:16</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> a deity’s image <b><a href='B:510 17:29'>Ac 17:29</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>c.</pp> coined gold, money <a href='B:470 10:9'>Mt 10:9</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>d.</pp></b> indeterminate <b>gold <a href='B:470 23:16'>Mt 23:16f</a>; <a href='B:660 5:3'>Js 5:3</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:χρυσόπρασος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:χρυσοῦς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}